Euphorbia cyparissias is a perennial herbaceous flowering plant.
Its stems are erect and unbranched.
The leaves are thin and narrow, measuring up to 10cm in length.
The plant has small, yellow-green flowers that bloom from spring to summer.
It is known for its milky sap that can be a skin irritant.
Euphorbia cyparissias is often found in meadows, hillsides, and open woodlands of Europe and Asia.
It is commonly used in landscaping due to its hardiness and ability to tolerate drought and poor soil conditions.
